article.description: — Kalob Ledoux had 23 points as Louisiana Tech beat Northwestern State 91-77 on Sunday.
article.headline: Ledoux leads Louisiana Tech past Northwestern State 91-77
article.linkText: Ledoux leads Louisiana Tech past Northwestern State 91-77
article.story: RUSTON, La. -- — Kalob Ledoux had 23 points as Louisiana Tech beat Northwestern State 91-77 on Sunday. Isaiah Crawford had 19 points for Louisiana Tech (2-0). Kenneth Lofton, Jr. added 16 points and JaColby Pemberton had 14 points. Jamaure Gregg scored a career-high 21 points for the Demons (0-3). Jairus Roberson added 12 points and LaTerrance Reed had 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
